1
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,000
Sir, five female prisoners..

2
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:01,120
..have been transferred
here from Jabalpur prison.

3
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:06,600
Tulsi!

4
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,800
Zubeida Bano!

5
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,320
Kalyani!

6
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:19,680
Jamuna!

7
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,000
Sukhiya!

8
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,840
Sir!

9
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:10,760
Who's it?
- This is Mahabal Singh!

10
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,520
Greetings!
- What's the matter?

11
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,760
There's some noise in the female ward.

12
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,920
Is it?
- Yes.

13
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,080
Wait, I'll get the key.

14
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:33,000
We can't live here anymore!
Open the door!

15
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:37,440
Let us out!
- Quiet!

16
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,320
Why can't you live here?

17
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:42,120
We're scared of blood!
- Stop!

18
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,200
Stop!

19
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:48,120
Open the door!

20
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,440
Quiet! The jailor's here!

21
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,840
The jailor's here!

22
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,800
Greetings, sir.

23
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,080
The constable told me
that someone's ill. - Yes.

24
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,440
The old woman Ramdai
vomited blood twice.

25
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,640
That's why the rest of
the women are very scared.

26
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,520
The doctor's here.

27
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:12,040
I'm sorry for being late.

28
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:16,000
Who's ill?
- Prisoner no. 8, Ramdai.

29
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:18,280
Today she vomited
blood while coughing.

30
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,240
Blood?
- Yes.

31
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:22,840
Come, Devendradra, let's take a look.
- What'll you do in there?

32
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,800
I'll go alone.
- Hurry up.

33
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,800
If I stand here for long,

34
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:29,480
then even I'll have to be
admitted in your hospital!

35
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,320
Everyone leave.

36
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:47,400
I won't survive now, doctor.
- Shut up!

37
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:53,400
Were you ill for a few
nights previously? - Yes.

38
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,840
I'm very thirsty.

39
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,600
Get water.

40
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,920
Don't worry, you'll be fine.

41
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,040
What's wrong with her?
- She's suffering from tuberculosis.

42
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,680
She'll have to be sent
to the hospital ward.

43
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:14,920
Fine. The female hospital is empty.

44
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,560
But we'll need a nurse too.

45
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,840
Warden.
- Yes.

46
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:28,160
Just inquire if anyone of
them is ready to serve her.

47
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:31,400
Who'd like to be with that old woman?

48
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:34,080
They all are so scared after
seeing her vomiting blood.

49
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,360
Ask them.
- As you say.

50
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:40,840
Is anyone of you
ready to be with Ramdai?

51
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,800
Why are you quiet?

52
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,600
I'm ready.

53
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:56,000
But she can't be with her.
- Why?

54
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,800
It's contagious.

55
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:01,160
And at this age, the tuberculosis
viruses spread very easily.

56
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,160
I don't care, doctor.

57
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,200
Don't worry about me.

58
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,000
Sir, just order me.

59
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,600
I'll be able to serve her very well.

60
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:17,640
Strange girl! She's come
here just a few days ago,

61
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,560
but she's friendly with everyone.

62
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:25,280
Here's my ticket. Write the order.

63
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:28,000
You might forget tomorrow.

64
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:30,520
Is this the time for
sir to write things?

65
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,440
Doctor, pen please.

66
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:57,320
Oh, God! Look at her audacity!

67
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:01,640
She was talking to the jailor as
if she's related to him! - Shut up!

68
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:05,120
Stop your nonsense! Go to your places!

69
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:10,760
1, 2, 3, 4, 5..

70
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:15,680
Why were you so shocked on
seeing that girl's card?

71
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:19,400
I was shocked to see the
accusation on that girl.

72
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,240
She's a murderer.

73
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,040
She poisoned someone.

74
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:30,440
And today she wants
to save someone else.

75
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,840
You know, the holy scriptures say..

76
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,920
..that even God can't
predict the character of women..

77
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,720
..and the destiny of men.

78
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,320
Then who are we?

79
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,960
I don't know about
the holy scriptures.

80
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:47,000
But I feel that if one
commits a crime once..

81
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,640
..that doesn't brand
him a criminal forever.

82
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:57,200
Why've you brought this bed?
- Doctor has sent it.

83
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,720
We're are slogging here..

84
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:10,280
..and Kalyani is sleeping
peacefully at the hospital!

85
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,160
Why are you jealous now?

86
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:15,520
Everyone was quiet
when the warden asked..

87
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,320
..you to look after that old woman!

88
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:20,720
Why are you feeling offended?

89
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,360
She still has high fever.

90
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,920
We'll have to take her to the
hospital tomorrow, for the X-ray.

91
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,200
You keep her ready.

92
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:04,840
Doctor, why did you send
another bed for the patient?

93
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,600
For you.

94
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,400
No. I don't need it.

95
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,400
I'll sleep on the floor.

96
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,840
Look, it's the prison rule that..

97
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,520
..everyone gets what they deserve.

98
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,200
Even if they don't want.

99
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,920
I'm an ordinary prisoner.

100
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,600
I'm here to serve the
punishment of my mistake.

101
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,640
I deserve only 3
blankets and a mattress.

102
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:30,000
Even I've some duties being a doctor.

103
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:34,080
And I did everything
to fulfill my duty.

104
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,720
Listen.

105
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,560
What happened?

106
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,800
I'm just a C-class prisoner.

107
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:49,240
Jailors and policemen
don't talk to me politely.

108
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,360
Why are you talking to me so politely?

109
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,920
I'm newly appointed in the prison.

110
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:58,400
So I couldn't learn its customs.

111
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:02,840
And I don't believe that one should
talk impolitely with C-class prisoners.

112
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,920
Number 12, Deputy
Mahesh is calling you.

113
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,160
Where..
- Next to the tap.

114
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:33,640
Why are you standing there? Come here.

115
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:38,120
How's your patient now?

116
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:40,520
She has very high fever.

117
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,360
I see.

118
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:48,080
Yes, after inquiring, I found
out that your case isn't true.

119
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:50,760
I also consulted a lawyer.

120
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:56,240
If I could know something else
from you.. - Thank you very much.

121
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,240
The case isn't false.

122
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:02,560
I wonder why the doctor
appointed you at the hospital.

123
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:07,200
It's dangerous for you to
serve a tuberculosis patient.

124
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,680
I took up this duty willingly.

125
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,480
Kalyani.

126
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,360
You forgot your ticket
at the ward yesterday.

127
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:19,360
Here. Keep it with you carefully.

128
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,040
How's that old woman?

129
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:24,320
I'll take a look.

130
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:31,480
Both the lungs are infected.

131
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:35,280
But I'm sure I'll cure her quickly.

132
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,960
I'll start giving her booster
shots from tomorrow.

133
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,440
Doctor.

134
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:20,520
The good news is that Ramdai
slept peacefully at night.

135
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,680
And she was fine in the morning.

136
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:26,160
You saved that poor lady.

137
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:29,840
I won't accept the entire
credit for saving her life.

138
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:32,880
You looked after her all day.

139
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,280
Nursing is the best
remedy for this ailment.

140
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:39,720
Ramdai, are you fine now?
- Yes, sir.

141
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,680
Let me check the temperature.

142
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,240
Should I keep resting even now?

143
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:46,880
No, go for walks.

144
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,400
But beware of the monsoon winds.

145
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:12,880
Kalyani.

146
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:14,880
Kalyani.

147
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,400
Listen.

148
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,840
Yes.

149
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,000
You look beautiful when
you're engrossed in work.

150
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:32,320
How long will Ramdai
keep her mouth shut?

151
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,240
Oh.

152
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:14,720
"O sweet little bird, what're you
chirping in the morning? Tell me."

153
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:18,040
"What're you chirping?"

154
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:27,560
"O sweet little bird, what're you
chirping in the morning? Tell me"

155
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:30,640
"What're you chirping?"

156
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:53,760
"I'm a mynah who lives in the cage.
My wings are useless."

157
00:14:53,960 --> 00:15:02,200
"There's a big gap between us.
How should I come to you?"

158
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:05,920
"How should I come to you?"

159
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:15,600
"O sweet little bird, what're you
chirping in the morning? Tell me.

160
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:18,560
"What're you chirping?"

161
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:41,360
"It's the spring. The garden is
blooming. The mango trees are lush."

162
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:49,680
"I peep through the window.
Spring has arrived."

163
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:54,000
"Spring has arrived."

164
00:15:54,240 --> 00:16:02,920
"O sweet little bird, what're you
chirping in the morning? Tell me."

165
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,680
"What're you chirping?"

166
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:09,760
Number 7? I just went to the
kitchen and you started singing!

167
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:13,680
Madam, I'm in a good
mood today. - I get that.

168
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:18,600
But the prison rule is to keep
your mouth shut, whatever the mood!

169
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,680
From tomorrow, you'll have
to grind those lentils again!

170
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:24,000
Sir, give some
medicines to Kalyani too.

171
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:27,360
She couldn't sleep in
the night, due to headache.

172
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,840
What happened to you?

173
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:32,440
Nothing. I caught a cold.

174
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:37,640
You shouldn't be careless about
your health. Let me check your pulse.

175
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:51,840
What a taste! Romancing a criminal!

176
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:58,280
You're educated, a doctor,
have a nice job.

177
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,920
Maintaining family's
dignity's also important.

178
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:05,160
Brother, this is called love!

179
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:08,120
"Love doesn't
distinguish between religions."

180
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,360
"When you're hungry, you
don't mind even soiled dishes."

181
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:12,720
"Love doesn't
distinguish between religions."

182
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,000
"When you're hungry, you
don't mind even soiled dishes."

183
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:19,040
What's the use if one
doesn't become blind in love?

184
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:22,160
Softly! He's coming!

185
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:28,040
He looks like Romeo!

186
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:32,280
This is not a place to romance,
but its prison!

187
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:34,480
If you want to do this, then go out.

188
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:39,160
Oh God! Don't you've any other topic?

189
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:43,440
The deputy jailor has gone to the
jailor to talk about this matter.

190
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:44,920
Be patient till then.

191
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,600
Kalyani, what are you doing here?

192
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:50,840
The doctor has sent special
food for you at the hospital!

193
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,040
Rich food!

194
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,200
She's so lucky!

195
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:59,080
Eggs and butter along
with chapatti! Great!

196
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,920
Oh my, I'm such a fool!

197
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,720
Had I served that old woman,
then even I would've enjoyed now!

198
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:08,200
And you would've
trapped some young man too!

199
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:32,720
Doctor.

200
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:39,040
Why did you send special food for me?

201
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:43,360
Are all those, who serve
tuberculosis patients in hospitals..

202
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:45,600
..served special food?

203
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:49,720
I don't know about others,
but this is the rule here.

204
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:54,360
But do I need this diet, or
are you doing a favor to me?

205
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:57,720
No. You do need it.

206
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:01,640
Can I ask you something Kalyani?
- Yes.

207
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:06,520
Why did you risk your life,
serving a tuberculosis patient?

208
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,560
Whatever the reason might be..

209
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,480
..but I won't let you
commit suicide here.

210
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,560
Why do you want to save a
downtrodden girl like me?

211
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:20,120
Do you know why I'm
serving this punishment?

212
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,160
I know.

213
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:27,080
You still want to save me?
- Yes.

214
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:31,840
Don't ruin your future,
repenting for your past.

215
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,680
How'll you benefit by this?
- Benefit?

216
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:40,640
In no way. Is profit and
loss everything in life?

217
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:44,520
Don't you feel
anything more than this?

218
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:49,040
The danger signal.

219
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:53,360
C'mon!

220
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:13,240
Long live!
- Revolution!

221
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:16,240
Long live!
- Revolution!

222
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:19,320
Hail Hanuman! Ocean
of wisdom! Protect us.

223
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,360
The emissary of Ram, very strong!
- What's it?

224
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:23,640
Those revolutionaries have
created havoc again! Oh god!

225
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:27,320
What's this danger signal for, Warden?

226
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,680
From the time the freedom
fighters have come to this prison..

227
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:31,200
..there's no peace!

228
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,840
They do something or the other!

229
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:37,240
Today Vinay Ghosh
slapped our deputy jailor!

230
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,400
Go back to your places!

231
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,520
19, 20, 21, 22, 23!

232
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,960
All's well!

233
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,800
All's well!

234
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:06,520
What's the matter, Kamla?
- Nothing.

235
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:12,040
I'll grind it. Ramdai is
fine now. I've no work there.

236
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:13,240
Move aside.

237
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:23,840
Kamla, if doctor comes to know,
he won't spare you!

238
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:25,800
What've you to do with that?

239
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,280
Shut up! Don't talk nonsense!
- You're talking nonsense!

240
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:30,280
No, Kamla.
- No!

241
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:33,080
It's enough of this daily nonsense!

242
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,600
Wonder what she thinks of herself!
What will you do?

243
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:37,880
Taunt again and see.
- I will!

244
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,720
Shut up, you dusky!
- What did you say?

245
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,960
I won't spare you!
- Leave me!

246
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,080
Kamla! Kamla!

247
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:45,720
I'll show you.

248
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,440
Leave. - Stop.

249
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:49,120
No!
- Kamla!

250
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:56,320
Murder!
- Quiet!

251
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:59,800
As soon as I disappeared,
you created havoc here!

252
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,720
I'll complain about each
one of you to the jailor!

253
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:16,760
I've noticed that you disappear
as soon as the doctor arrives!

254
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,560
Yesterday doctor was
asking me about you.

